tagDescription: Correspondence relating to the preparation of the Canadian case before the Tribunal. Most of the Correspondence with F. C. Wade. 2 files.
Memorandum on the boundary between Canada and Alaska showing the contention of the Canadian Government in respect thereto. Printed for use of the Colonial Office.
Certified Copy of Letters patent appointing Sifton British Agent to the Tribunal.
Correspondence relating to preparation of the Canadian case before the Tribunal. Various correspondents.

Reprint of Correspondence respecting the Proceedings of the Joint Commission for the settlement of questions pending between the United States and Canada, March 1898 - March 1899. Printed for use of the Foreign Office.
